===================================
Dash documentation Domain & Builder
===================================

:author: @togakushi

About
=====

You can read the 'Documentation Set' style document by using `dash API browser`.

* For Mac OS X users: dash_
* For Windows or Linux users: Zeal_

This extension has been inspired by dashbuilder_

.. _dash: http://kapeli.com/dash
.. _Zeal: http://zealdocs.org/
.. _dashbuilder: https://bitbucket.org/shimizukawa/sphinxcontrib-dashbuilder


Install
=======

::

   $ pip install sphinxcontrib-dashdomain


Configuration
=============

conf.py configuration values:

:dash_name:
   (optional) name for docset explicitly. default is same as `project`.
:dash_icon_file:
   (optional) PNG file path for docset icon. default is `sphinxcontrib/dash/icon.png`.


conf.py example::

   extensions = ['sphinxcontrib.dash.builder', 'sphinxcontrib.dash.domain']

   dash_name = 'docs'
   dash_icon_file = '_static/icon.png'


Makefile add::

   .PHONY: docset
   dash:
       $(SPHINXBUILD) -b docset $(ALLSPHINXOPTS) $(BUILDDIR)/docset
       @echo
       @echo "Build finished. The Dash pages are in $(BUILDDIR)/docset."


